messages.message:
btw this is still occurring roughly once a day, and sometimes this causes my laptop fans to go crazy :dash:

when my laptop fans were super noisy over the weekend, i looked at the file-service logs and saw this - killing `grpc-file-service` made the fans calm down

This looks a bit like grpc-file-service has lost connectivity with rabbitmq and the queue is just continuing to build up. This is also what the log messages all seem to indicate, that something is wrong with rabbit.

@Victor Zeng if you can help take a look at this that’d be great.
